\begin_layout Subsection
Human Recognition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The intelligibility of a speech signal to a human is difficult to accurately
 and quantitatively measure.
 The most obvious measure is to have human test subjects listen to signals
 and judge which are more intelligible.
 In order to achieve reputable, repeatable and accurate results a large
 test is required with a large number of test subjects and recordings.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{ITU}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 standard for such tests is the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{MOS}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "InternationalTelecommunicationUnion1996"

\end_inset

.
 The test is designed to give an indication of the quality of telecommunication
 transmission, but is applicable as a measure of speech intelligibility.
 The 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{MOS}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 results are a score calculated by the mean of the listeners’ scores in
 the range one to five, with one representing the worst quality and five
 representing the highest quality of intelligibility.
 There are multiple 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{MOS}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 tests outlined in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "InternationalTelecommunicationUnion1996"

\end_inset

, including: a standard scale, measuring overall subjective quality; a listening
 effort scale, measuring the effort required by a listener to understand
 the speech; a loudness preference scale, measuring the preferred loudness
 of the signal; and a comparative scale, measuring comparatively to a reference
 signal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Additionally, the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{ITU}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 outline a separate standard for measuring communication systems with noise
 suppression 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "InternationalTelecommunicationUnion2003"

\end_inset

.
 This standard recommends 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{MOS}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 tests scoring on the quality of three separate areas, (1) the speech signal,
