\begin_layout Subsection
Ideal Binary Mask
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ideal binary mask algorithms operate on the time-frequency representation
 of a signal, often called the spectrogram.
 This representation can be formulated by taking the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{STFT}
\end_layout

\end_inset

