 units, i.e.
 frequencies present at a given time.
 The ideal binary mask is a mask, the same size as the input spectrogram,
 with a 1 in time-frequency unit if the desired signal is stronger than
 the noise in that unit, and a 0 otherwise.
 The mask is then multiplied by the spectrogram, leaving only time-frequency
 units where the desired signal is strongest.
 This requires estimation of the signal and noise: which may be done through
 any of the estimators outlined above.
 Alternatively, this may be done using a voice activity detector 
