\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another method to ensure component information is captured within the component
 matrix is to introduce sparseness constraints on the activation matrix.
 By its nature, the activation matrix should be sparser than the component
 matrix.
 Through the non-negative constraint of 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
ac{NMF}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, sparseness of the activation matrix (and indeed, also the component matrix)
 naturally occurs 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Albright2006,Hoyer2004"

\end_inset

.
 However, it can be desirable to allow explicit control over the sparseness,
 especially in speech applications 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Schmidt2006"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Hoyer2002"

\end_inset

 proposed an algorithm based on the multiplicative update algorithm in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Lee1999"

\end_inset

 with an introduced cost function to aid in control of the sparseness.
 This algorithm was further improved in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Hoyer2004"

\end_inset

 where the explicit control of sparseness was introduced.
 This was achieved by defining the sparseness measure 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Hoyer2004"

\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
sparseness(x)=\frac{\sqrt{n}-\left(\sum\left|x_{i}\right|\right)/\sqrt{\sum x_{i}^{2}}}{\sqrt{n}-1}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is the length of vector 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The developed algorithm is then based on the Euclidean distance objective
 function, employing a combination of multiplicative update functions (§
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Multiplicative-Update-Algorithms"

\end_inset

