 However, the theory developed is applicable to many types of objective
 functions and implementation algorithms 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Cichocki2006"

\end_inset

.
 Similarly, the cost functions introduced need not be specific to sparsity,
 but can be applied to many auxiliary constraints, such as enforcing smoothness
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Fevotte2011"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

